# BerlinBrew .forceignore
#
# Anything listed here is excluded from real-Salesforce deploys
# (sf project deploy / sf project retrieve) but still part of the
# project source for Nimbus.
#
# This file is one of the points of the demo: Nimbus can run code
# that wouldn't deploy to your org without dependencies that don't
# exist in your org. That's the whole reason fast local execution
# matters in the first place.

# ─── HopLog managed-package showcase ───────────────────────────────
#
# `Hoplog` is a fictional logging managed package. Its full surface —
# Apex classes AND the namespaced custom object — lives under
# `stubs/Hoplog/`, which `stubs/` (below) already excludes from sf
# deploys. The Apex classes here that CALL into Hoplog must also be
# excluded, because a real-org deploy would fail with "Variable does
# not exist: Hoplog.Logger" since the package isn't installed.
# Tests run cleanly on Nimbus via the `nimbus.stubs.namespaces=Hoplog`
# declaration in nimbus.properties plus the local schema XML.
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditLogger.cls
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditLogger.cls-meta.xml
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditLoggerTest.cls
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditLoggerTest.cls-meta.xml
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditArchive.cls
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditArchive.cls-meta.xml
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditArchiveTest.cls
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewAuditArchiveTest.cls-meta.xml

# ─── Stubs directory ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# stubs/ contains test-only type definitions for managed packages
# that don't exist in the test org — Apex classes AND namespaced
# objects/fields. One folder per package: stubs/<Pkg>/. Never deployed.
stubs/

# ─── API-version mismatch demonstration ────────────────────────────
#
# BrewLegacyAuditLog deliberately uses System.Assert.areEqual (v56+)
# while declaring apiVersion 52.0 in its meta.xml. Real Salesforce
# would reject the deploy as a method-not-found error at the API
# version mismatch. The whole point of this file is to demonstrate
# Nimbus's API-version mismatch warning, which fires before deploy —
# don't try to ship it.
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewLegacyAuditLog.cls
force-app/main/default/classes/BrewLegacyAuditLog.cls-meta.xml

